<paragraph blockId="84.[151,1436,279,664]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,410,279,304]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">Diagnostic characters</emphasis>
. Oval shell; sunken spire; ear-shaped aperture; barely reflexed basal and apical lips; nearly orthocline outer lip; thin parietal callus; unperforated base; spiral rows of shallow rounded pits, more widely spaced in the middle of the shell; spiral furrows towards the base. Protoconch: heterostrophic, submerged (hardly visible in immature specimens only); globose; surface smooth.
</paragraph>
